		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">3gengames wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Just curious, did you use 2KB more PPU RAM?<br /><br />And that's cool that you did GBA development too. What games did you work on?<br /><br />Yeah but still cool that you used an NES, good job. Hopefully most are of at least this quality. And so did you find the NESDev wiki hard to use and what details weren't highlighted in it?</div>
<br />
<br />No PPU RAM, only PPU ROM (2x 4kb). Is that a MMC3 feature? We only used bank switching from MMC3, no other mapper specific features.
<br />
<br />Here are some of the prototypes and releases we made for GBA/NDS/PDA: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.velinje.com/pixelknights">http://www.velinje.com/pixelknights</a><!-- m -->

		

